      heading: 'Etsy SEO Specifics for Math Worksheet Sellers',
      content: 'Etsy\u2019s search algorithm works differently from Google\u2019s, and understanding these differences is essential for ranking your math worksheet listings.\n\nEtsy\u2019s algorithm uses listing quality score, which combines click-through rate, favorite rate, and conversion rate. A listing that gets clicked on frequently from search results and converts those clicks into sales ranks higher over time. This means your listing thumbnail and title are not just marketing tools \u2014 they directly affect your search ranking through their impact on click-through rate.\n\nTag matching on Etsy is phrase-based, not keyword-based. The tag \u201cmath worksheets kindergarten\u201d matches searches for \u201cmath worksheets for kindergarten\u201d and \u201ckindergarten math worksheets\u201d but not \u201cworksheets for math.\u201d Use your 13 tags to cover different phrase orderings and synonyms that buyers might search for.\n\nEtsy gives a temporary ranking boost to new and renewed listings. When you first publish a listing, Etsy shows it to more buyers for a short period to gauge engagement. Use this boost wisely by launching listings with optimized titles, all 13 tags filled, professional photos, and complete descriptions. A strong first impression during the new listing boost period sets the trajectory for long-term ranking.\n\nShop sections help Etsy understand your shop\u2019s category focus. Create sections like \u201cAddition Worksheets,\u201d \u201cSubtraction Worksheets,\u201d \u201cMath Puzzles,\u201d \u201cComparison Worksheets,\u201d and \u201cMath Drill Sheets.\u201d Organized sections improve your shop\u2019s browsability and signal category expertise to Etsy\u2019s algorithm.',
